In our case, we can take `G = B ⊗ K (FiniteAdeleRing (𝓞 K) K)`, and `f` to be the multiplication by `u` on the left or right. The fact that `u` is in the group of units of `B ⊗ K (FiniteAdeleRing (𝓞 K) K)` and `B` is central simple implies that the multiplication by `u` preserves the add Haar measure.

